\begin{tcbProblem}[label={problem:0009:question:Eng}]
	A Pythagorean triplet is a set of three natural numbers, \( a \less b \less c \), for which,
	\begin{equation*}
		{a}^{2} \mathplus {b}^{2} \equal {c}^{2}
	\end{equation*}
	For example,
	\( {3}^{2} \mathplus {4}^{2} \equal 9 \mathplus 16 \equal 25 \equal {5}^{2} \).

	There exists exactly one Pythagorean triplet for which \( a \mathplus b \mathplus c \equal 1000 \).
	Find the product \( abc \).
	\par%
	\hrefOriginalPage{9}%
	\tcbline%
	ピタゴラス数（ピタゴラスの定理を満たす自然数）とは\( a \less b \less c \)で以下の式を満たす数の組である.
	\begin{equation*}
		{a}^{2} \mathplus {b}^{2} \equal {c}^{2}
	\end{equation*}
	例えば，\( {3}^{2} \mathplus {4}^{2} \equal 9 \mathplus 16 \equal 25 \equal {5}^{2} \)である.

	\( a \mathplus b \mathplus c \equal 1000 \)となるピタゴラスの三つ組が一つだけ存在する.
	これらの積\( abc \)を計算しなさい.
	\par%
